what presidents death touched you the most and what were you doing at the time president john f kennedy i was in the sixth grade at the time and was in class when the principle came in and announced that the president had been shot i felt hurt and laid awake all night thinking about it president kennedy was special he gave us hope and vision he was the example of a fair and caring leader he was popular and well liked we confided in him and had trust in the government we lost most of that during the days past the assignation when all the cover ups and everything surfaced this was a slap in the face for america and a big slap in the face for the federal government get real people here we have our leader our representative and speaker for america scheduled to visit dallas and just out of nowhere his route changes even without the presidents or his staffs knowledge then he gets shot the the witnesses that remember seeing a police officer with a hearing aid reveals that non of the police had hearing aids wake up the oswald gets caught and while in jail gets silenced by jack ruby oh please then the warren commission issues a report that oswald was the lone shooter oh please the government lied then and they continue lying up to today i feel sorry for jackolean and the children it must have been horrible and frightening dealing with this tragedy no other first lady has ever achieved getting the respect and love she got i have never trusted the federal government since then and most americans feel the same someone needs to fess up to the lies and cover ups and let america move on just my thought uncle sam you messed this one up bad and will never be forgiven savvy John F. Kennedy assassination Kennedy assassination theories Jack Ruby Lee Harvey Oswald John F. Kennedy Warren Commission Detailed timeline of the assassination of John F. Kennedy EastEnders Reaction to the assassination of John F. Kennedy Columbine High School massacre Sin City Plame affair 39th Canadian federal